      passage: `Each year, the Nobel Prize in Literature is given to an author who has, in the words of its founder Alfred Nobel, &ldquo;produced the most outstanding work in an idealistic _____ in 1912, for instance, judges recognized Gerhart Johann Robert Hauptmann [for] his fruitful, varied and outstanding production in the realm of dramatic art.&rdquo;`,
