      passage: `The work of Tobias Gerstenberg et al. on tracking eye movements supports a theory that people engage in _____ thinking when making causal judgments: when subjects were asked to look at two colliding billiard balls and judge whether one caused or prevented the other&rsquo;s movement through a gate, their eyes looked at where the target ball would have gone if the ball that altered its path did not exist.`,
